<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-06-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-16"><hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 16,
                                1894</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The provisional Government of Salvador informs me that the President of
                            the United States has recognized that Government, and now ask
                            extradition refugees. Is it so? What shall I do?</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>